{"content": "# Kiyotaka WebSocket API

## Connection
```
wss://ap-sin3.ws.api.kiyotaka.ai/nonbook/ws?encoding=json
```

## Authentication
```json
{
  "method": "public/authenticate",
  "params": {
    "token": "YOUR_API_KEY"
  }
}
```

## Subscribe
```json
{
  "jsonrpc": "2.0",
  "id": 0,
  "method": "public/subscribe",
  "params": {
    "channels": [{
      "type": "TRADE",
      "exchange": "BINANCE_FUTURES",
      "symbol": "BTCUSDT",
      "category": "*"
    }],
    "compression": "brotli",
    "version": "v2"
  }
}
```

## Available Channels
- TRADE — Real-time trade stream
- ORDERBOOK — Orderbook depth snapshots
- FUNDING_RATE — Funding rate + predicted
- OPEN_INTEREST — OI updates
- LIQUIDATIONS — Liquidation events
- VOLUME_PROFILE — Volume profile from live trades

## Trade Response
```json
{
  "points": [{
    "series": {
      "type": "TRADE",
      "side": "BUY",
      "coin": "BTC",
      ...
    },
    "trade": {
      "price": 90003,
      "amount": 0.002,
      ...
    }
  }]
}
```

## Best Practices
- Use Brotli compression for efficiency
- Implement heartbeat handling
- Auto-reconnect on disconnect
- Use category: "*" for all sub-types
